# Fair Structure Loot (FSL)

Mod directory: `FairStructureLoot/` · Package: `net.berkle.fairstructureloot`

## Version source of truth

Workspace root `versions.properties` and this mod's `gradle.properties`:

- Minecraft **26.1.2** (Mojang official names only — no Yarn/intermediary in source)
- Fabric Loader **0.19.2+**, Fabric API **0.149.0+26.1.2**
- Loom `net.fabricmc.fabric-loom` **1.16-SNAPSHOT**
- Java **25** (`implementation`, not `modImplementation`)

After version bumps: run `scripts/sync-versions.ps1`, `scripts/gradle.ps1 FairStructureLoot build`, `scripts/sync-minecraft-api.ps1`.

## Goals

- Per-player instanced loot for structure containers (Lootr-like, scoped to registered groups)
- End ship elytra item frames → instanced barrel (one elytra per player); toggle: `end_ship` (separate from `end_city`)
- Ancient city, bastion, trial chambers (+ optional vanilla groups) → per-player rolls from vanilla tables
- Trial vaults and spawner rewards → per-player; completion eject follows vanilla cadence (one player per cycle)

## Architecture (do not fight this)

| Layer | Responsibility |
|-------|----------------|
| `StructureGroupRegistry` | Loot table → structure group; mod API registration |
| `StructureActivationSavedData` | Per-world group on/off (overworld SavedData) |
| `InstancedLootSavedData` | Per-container folders; overworld persistence keyed by `dimension:x,y,z` |
| `InstancedLootGenerator` | Vanilla `LootTable.fill` with per-player or shared seed |
| Mixins | Cancel shared fill; redirect menus; vault/spawner hooks |
| Client | HUD ▲ indicator (green/orange/black + gray shadow), break-hint toast, S2C cache mirrors, no server logic |

**Persistence:** all instanced inventories live in **overworld** SavedData regardless of container dimension.

## Mixin & runtime rules

- `./gradlew build` passing is **not** enough — mixins validate at **runtime**
- Before new/changed mixins: read `.minecraft-api/<version>/api-index.txt` or `javap` on cached client jar
- Prefer Fabric events over mixins when sufficient (`ModServerEvents`, break handlers)
- **Never** call `level.getBlockState()` from `BLOCK_ENTITY_UNLOAD` — use `getChunkNow()` on loaded chunk (C2ME deadlock)
- Do not `@ModifyVariable` synthetic lambdas; use `@Redirect` / `@Inject` on named methods
- Trial spawner: completion via `TrialSpawnerMixin.ejectReward`; ominous via `TrialSpawnerStateMixin` + `TrialSpawnerPlayers`

## Conventions

- Split `main` + `client` source sets
- Use `Identifier` (not `ResourceLocation`)
- Server-side loot and persistence; client entrypoint minimal (packets + HUD)
- New structure groups: register in `StructureGroupRegistry` or `FairStructureLootAPI.registerGroup`
- Audit notes and history: **`FSLAudit.md`** (not README)

## README assets & break-hint toast

- **Do not embed base64 images in README** — use `docs/assets/*.png` (regenerate: `python scripts/generate-readme-assets.py`)
- Mod icon: `docs/assets/icon.png` and `src/main/resources/assets/fairstructureloot/icon.png`
- HUD triangles: `docs/assets/hud-{green,orange,black}-triangle.png` (5×3 px, gray `#404040` shadow)
- Break-hint toast (`FairLootChestBreakToast`): three-triangle icon (green/orange/black + gray shadow) from `textures/gui/toast_icon.png`; exact body text:
